<H1>Zvi Galil</H1>

<HR>

<p>

<STRONG>Zvi Galil</STRONG> is the Julian Clarence Levi
Professor of 
Mathematical Methods and Computer Science at the 
<!WA0><A href="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/">
Computer Science Department</A>
of 
<!WA1><A href="http://www.cc.columbia.edu/">
Columbia University</A>
 in the city of New York. He currently serves as the Morris A. and
Alma Schapiro Professor and Dean of the 
<!WA2><A HREF="http://www.seas.columbia.edu/">
School of Engineering and Applied Science</A> at Columbia University.
His main research interests are in the design and
analysis of 
<!WA3><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~galil/galil.algorithms.html">
algorithms</A>, 
<!WA4><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~galil/galil.complexity.html">
computational complexity</A>
 and 
<!WA5><A
HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~galil/galil.crypto.html">
cryptography</A>. <BR> Zvi is the Editor in Chief of
<!WA6><A HREF="http://www.siam.org/journals/sicomp/sicomp.html">
SIAM Journal on Computing</A> and the
<!WA7><A HREF="http://www.apnet.com/www/journal/al.htm">
Journal of Algorithms</A>. <BR><BR>




